An 18-years-old man was arrested in Mpumalanga at the weekend for the murder of his wealthy grandmother, Kgarebe Stephelina Masangu, 79, in Roossenekal in May.He will appear in the Groblersdal Magistrate s Court today.Police spokesperson Lt-Col Moatshe Ngoepe said: The elderly woman was attacked and killed by people using various objects while sleeping. Detectives found evidence that linked the deceased s grandson and a female relative in her late forties to the murder, Ngoepe said. The two suspects disappeared shortly after the grandmother s funeral. Police traced them to their hiding place in Mpumalanga. The woman managed to escape while the 18-year-old youth was arrested, Ngoepe said. Preliminary investigations have found that the motive for the murder was to acquire the grandmother s property, which is valued at millions of rands, Ngoepe said.In another case, police have launched a search for a 24-year-old man from Mokwakwaila village near Tzaneen who allegedly raped and impregnated his 14-year-old cousin.He allegedly started raping the girl in February 2016. In May, it was discovered that the girl was pregnant. Police are appealing to community members with information that may lead to the arrest of the man to contact Mokwakwaila police on 0153869951 or Crime Stop on 0860010111, Ngoepe said.Meanwhile, Mokwakwaila police have also launched a search for a 38-year-old man who allegedly attacked his girlfriend stabbing her repeatedly with a sharp object at Ga-Pelana village.The two had a heated argument and the 26-year-old woman ran to her parents house but he followed her. Upon arrival, he slashed her all over her body before running away. She is still being treated in hospital after suffering multiple injuries, Ngoepe said.MONTSHO MATLALAmontshom@thenewage.co.za